1
00:00:01,150 --> 00:00:04,630
1 year ago

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:13,900
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

3
00:00:18,090 --> 00:00:21,600
Mom. Mom, Yi Yeong has gone missing.

4
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:25,740
- Mom, she's not here, she's not here.
- What?

5
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:29,910
My gosh! What?

6
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:50,650
Let's ride the cable car tomorrow morning.

7
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:05,920
No.

8
00:01:08,740 --> 00:01:11,360
I didn't do it.

9
00:01:13,470 --> 00:01:16,180
I didn't kill him.

10
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:21,000
I didn't kill him, I didn't kill him.

11
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:32,090
What should I do?

12
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,250
What should I do?

13
00:02:04,550 --> 00:02:06,640
Do you remember me?

14
00:02:10,610 --> 00:02:13,120
Should I change the question?

15
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:22,310
Do you remember whom you killed?

16
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:26,400
Do you remember?

17
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:57,100
I Wanna Hear Your Song

18
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:59,040
Hong Yee Yeong

19
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:02,750
Episode 5

20
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:43,830
I can finally breathe now.

21
00:03:43,830 --> 00:03:48,620
I was so surprised when she was like that after our phone call.

22
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,390
You were very surprised, right?

23
00:03:52,390 --> 00:03:56,580
You would've been so surprised to see her like that while she was jogging. I'm sorry.

24
00:03:56,580 --> 00:04:02,310
No, it's alright. Although she didn't want to, I took her to the Namsan Tower.

25
00:04:02,310 --> 00:04:04,730
I should be the one to be sorry.

26
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:09,870
Would she have gone if she didn't want to? She went because it's worth going.

27
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:12,270
I heard that you are both in the Sinyeong  Philharmonic Orchestra.

28
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:14,130
What do you play?

29
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:17,650
I play the piano.

30
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:20,960
Yeah, piano.

31
00:04:22,050 --> 00:04:24,150
Piano...

32
00:04:25,570 --> 00:04:29,430
Now that I think about it, you helped Yi Yeong last time too, right?

33
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:32,260
When she fainted in the rain.

34
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:34,500
I didn't exactly help her...

35
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:39,770
Since our routes were similar, we often meet each other.

36
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,160
Oh really?

37
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:46,970
That's why she thought it was more significant than it was.

38
00:04:49,230 --> 00:04:50,470
It's not that.

39
00:04:50,470 --> 00:04:54,890
There is a guy that she often saw and was worried that he was a stalker.

40
00:04:54,890 --> 00:04:56,230
A stalker?

41
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:58,990
Don't feel so wronged, she is usually like that.

42
00:04:58,990 --> 00:05:02,280
She often worried about useless things since she was young.

43
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:05,830
Nonetheless, I feel more relieved after seeing you myself.

44
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:07,810
Your name is...?

45
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:11,920
It's Yun, Jang Yun.

46
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,250
You should answer it. If you're busy you may leave as well.

47
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:18,850
I'm sorry but I'll have to leave.

48
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:27,330
Jang Yun... Jang Yun?

49
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:30,440
I feel I've heard the name before.

50
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:39,990
I roughly finished cleaning, I'm going to the gas station.

51
00:05:39,990 --> 00:05:42,820
The business card is on top of the piano.

52
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:15,850
Let's ride the cable car tomorrow morning, Hong Yi Yeong.

53
00:06:15,850 --> 00:06:17,160
Who are you?

54
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,590
Well...

55
00:06:18,590 --> 00:06:21,610
Who am I?

56
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:35,750
Don't come close.

57
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,100
Why did you come again?

58
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:39,490
You need to speak.

59
00:06:39,490 --> 00:06:42,130
I don't know.

60
00:06:42,130 --> 00:06:45,220
I can't remember.

61
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:48,400
Please spare me.

62
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,700
Please spare me.

63
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:53,890
Shall we change the question?

64
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:58,150
Do you remember whom you killed?

65
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:14,370
I wanted your opinion about holding Maestro Nam's inaugural concert before the music festival.

66
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:19,630
A lot of fans are asking for it, and it would bring attention to the music festival. How do you feel about it?

67
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:22,310
It sounds fine.

68
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:26,620
Don't worry about the sponsors and do whatever is comfortable for you.

69
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:28,060
Thank you, Chairwoman.

70
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:31,010
When we decide on the piece to perform, I will let you know.

71
00:07:31,010 --> 00:07:32,810
Don't go around spending too much money.

72
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:36,880
But also don't make it look cheap, since we have an image to uphold.

73
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:42,660
How is Nam Ju Wan? Can you control him?

74
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:44,570
I will have to work harder.

75
00:07:44,570 --> 00:07:46,780
You should maintain a balance.

76
00:07:46,780 --> 00:07:51,760
If a young person plays hard to get, he's bound to be harshly criticized.

77
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,320
Even in the recent audition,

78
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:57,390
he was so stubborn. I heard the one he fired jumped into the Han River.

79
00:07:57,390 --> 00:08:01,510
Luckily she wasn't seriously injured and I'm getting some compensation ready.

80
00:08:01,510 --> 00:08:04,110
Watch your mouth so the reporters don't come to know.

81
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:06,870
I'll do that.

82
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:09,470
Don't you know the jealousy that goes around here?

83
00:08:09,470 --> 00:08:15,150
You must use the product well.  Enjoy the sweet taste for a long long time and then spit it out.

84
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:26,330
The conductor is not a piece of chewing gum. What is the sweet taste?

85
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:29,420
That old hag.

86
00:08:33,850 --> 00:08:35,570
It's me, where are you?

87
00:08:35,570 --> 00:08:39,780
Let's meet. I'm feeling down today. I need a drink.

88
00:08:52,190 --> 00:08:54,780
I thought you were Manager Yun.

89
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:58,200
You are a pro at finding someone.

90
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,720
You can see everything in the security's monitor.

91
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:03,890
If you snoop around at a place like that, people won't like you.

92
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:08,120
That's why you shouldn't turn off your cellphone.

93
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:20,530
I'm feeling cramped here, let's go out.

94
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:35,250
I never would've expected that you'd want to come here.

95
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:38,820
Why, because it doesn't  match me?

96
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:44,120
I come here often, when I'm tired of practicing.

97
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:47,420
Do you know that you can see rainbows here?

98
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,780
Rainbows?

99
00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:53,450
When you're lucky, you can see them.

100
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:56,340
Although I haven't seen it this year.

101
00:09:58,270 --> 00:10:00,950
I have a question.

102
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:04,910
You sure have a lot of questions. What is it?

103
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:06,940
It's about Jang Yun.

104
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:11,150
That person, you picked him right?

105
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,460
Why are you asking about Jang Yun all of a sudden?

106
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:17,370
How did you bring that person?

107
00:10:17,370 --> 00:10:23,350
He didn't go to music college nor does he have experience. He didn't even do the formal audition.

108
00:10:26,060 --> 00:10:29,040
How is it that there is nothing you don't know?

109
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,340
Hmm, how did I bring him again?

110
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:37,850
Probably heard him on the way to judge the audition.

111
00:10:48,140 --> 00:10:51,660
There was not much skill, but I was moved.

112
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:55,250
My emotions were just suddenly moved.

113
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:57,220
Why are you asking about him all of a sudden?

114
00:10:57,220 --> 00:11:04,090
Jang Yun's performance is similar to a certain person's.

115
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:08,350
You felt it too, right?

116
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:16,650
I was curious whether you picked him for that reason.

117
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:18,220
Don't overthink.

118
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:22,310
There are many similar artists everywhere.

119
00:11:23,810 --> 00:11:25,840
Stop writing fiction and get up.

120
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:29,880
I'm a very busy person, whether you know it or not.

121
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:55,960
Tone-deaf

122
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:04,300
Insomniac

123
00:12:08,140 --> 00:12:12,430
From seeing your prior interview, the reason you became interested

124
00:12:12,430 --> 00:12:15,420
in aphasic children is your cousin.

125
00:12:15,420 --> 00:12:18,320
Please tell me that story.

126
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:22,850
I have a female cousin who was raised like my sister.

127
00:12:22,850 --> 00:12:27,580
She lost her parents when she was five because of a car crash and ended up living with us,

128
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:31,190
but she was unable to speak for a year because of the trauma.

129
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:33,970
And that's the first time I learned of the illness called "aphasia."

130
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:38,650
My memory of that time was a big motivator later in my choice of a major.

131
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:44,970
When do you think was the hardest time?

132
00:12:44,970 --> 00:12:47,720
The hardest time...

133
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:52,830
When my cousin's aphasia reoccurred.

134
00:12:53,580 --> 00:12:57,800
A year ago my cousin was in another big accident

135
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:04,580
It was a car crash and during the month after the accident, she couldn't speak.

136
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:10,130
The after-effects remain until now.  She can't remember the time before and following the accident.

137
00:13:10,130 --> 00:13:13,720
She has chronic insomnia and repeated nightmares.

138
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:17,860
Although I am a physician, my heart aches so  much for her.

139
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:47,000
My head... it is split.

140
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:49,710
Are you awake?

141
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:55,550
Unni?

142
00:14:04,970 --> 00:14:06,970
It's so delicious.

143
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:13,120
Are you a beggar? Eat more presentably.

144
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,960
They're two days worth of pills for your headache.

145
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:18,040
Am I a dog? Let me eat in peace.

146
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:22,290
What are you doing these days? You never jog so why do it?

147
00:14:22,290 --> 00:14:24,260
I said I was forced to go.

148
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:28,070
If you didn't want to go, you should have refused, airhead.

149
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:29,800
What is your relationship with Jang Yun?

150
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:33,640
What relationship? There is nothing going on.

151
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:36,900
When you have nothing going on, you go jogging all the way to Namsan together?

152
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:39,940
You were all worried about him being a stalker.

153
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:42,180
Please get your head together.

154
00:14:42,180 --> 00:14:45,240
Don't go around from one guy to another.

155
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:48,400
Alright, I got it. Don't worry about me.

156
00:14:51,070 --> 00:14:54,880
Why did you leave your phone at the ward? It kept ringing, so I answered it.

157
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:57,720
Your rehearsal starts an hour early.

158
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:00,730
What?

159
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:01,990
What?

160
00:15:01,990 --> 00:15:04,400
What do you mean what?

161
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:06,000
Why are you saying this now?

162
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:09,190
What's with the screaming and shouting? You will revive the dead.

163
00:15:09,190 --> 00:15:11,350
Hey! Clean this up before you go.

164
00:15:17,540 --> 00:15:20,610
What do I do?

165
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:27,410
Hong Yi Yeong!

166
00:15:29,660 --> 00:15:32,980
Look's like you came out of the hospital.  How do you feel? Are you okay?

167
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:36,480
I don't know. Don't talk to me.

168
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,960
What.. why?

169
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:42,310
Don't make me say anything. I don't hear anything.

170
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:01,000
I'm late. I'm  sorry.

171
00:16:05,340 --> 00:16:07,150
Oh, wait a second!

172
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:13,750
This is my instrument. I'm using this to rehearse today.

173
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:14,920
Today?

174
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:17,360
There's only one set of  timpani today.

175
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:20,440
Look, I'm right.

176
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,830
Take it out.

177
00:16:21,830 --> 00:16:24,020
Alright one, two, three.

178
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:42,650
Good morning, everyone.

179
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:51,590
Today I dressed up for all of you.

180
00:16:51,590 --> 00:16:53,370
How is it?

181
00:16:57,120 --> 00:17:00,070
You all got the pieces we are playing today. right?

182
00:17:00,070 --> 00:17:02,360
Yes.

183
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,590
Miss Hong Yi Yeong?

184
00:17:07,830 --> 00:17:10,210
May I have a moment with you?

185
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,060
Scheherazade?

186
00:17:36,060 --> 00:17:39,120
Yes, I heard it when I was coming in for work.

187
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:42,880
Another person answered the phone and we told her a few things.

188
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,990
I don't think the right message got through.

189
00:17:44,990 --> 00:17:49,310
The conductor didn't tell you?

190
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:55,290
This is the statement  for a day and a half of pay.

191
00:17:55,290 --> 00:17:58,280
The date of deposit is the 25th.

192
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:02,770
The locker must be emptied today.

193
00:18:40,530 --> 00:18:43,540
My age is 27.

194
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:47,480
It is an anxious age when you have no job work at,

195
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:52,590
no one to love, and nothing to hold on to.

196
00:18:57,990 --> 00:19:01,750
Mr. Tone Deaf

197
00:19:04,730 --> 00:19:10,470
Until the age of 27, I have only wanted one thing.

198
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:14,830
For someone to recognize me.

199
00:19:16,690 --> 00:19:21,490
For someone to acknowledge me and tell me I did well.

200
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,300
That is the only thing.

201
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:39,120
Very good.

202
00:19:42,130 --> 00:19:43,880
Like this.

203
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:46,490
How is that?

204
00:19:48,450 --> 00:19:51,160
Jenny's Message Arriving

205
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:54,930
Mental collapse is mental collapse and food is food.

206
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:57,610
Eat pig and gain the strength of a pig.

207
00:19:57,610 --> 00:19:59,930
She's so cute.

208
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:04,090
This cutie

209
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:08,600
Jae Hyeong's Message Arriving.

210
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:10,530
What is this jerk saying?

211
00:20:10,530 --> 00:20:13,500
Noona, today I'm finally doing a performance.

212
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:16,970
It's my first paid gig. You're coming, right?

213
00:20:16,970 --> 00:20:19,220
I want to show you.

214
00:20:19,220 --> 00:20:22,180
I want to receive compliments from you.

215
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:24,640
I'll wait for you. You have to come.

216
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:29,740
I'm going to wait until you come. Let's have Samgyeopsal (grilled pork belly) after my show.

217
00:20:29,740 --> 00:20:33,110
I'll buy! I swear, I'm not lying.

218
00:20:41,930 --> 00:20:44,380
Event to Celebrate Opening

219
00:20:57,930 --> 00:21:00,260
Does youth always look like this?

220
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:03,770
Small and ugly?

221
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,900
It's not worth seeing.

222
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:13,400
For insignificant youth, everyone is anxious, everyone falters.

223
00:21:13,430 --> 00:21:19,530
The dream is far and money is even farther.

224
00:21:19,530 --> 00:21:24,940
Life isn't about living, it's about surviving

225
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:33,800
I mean this kind of youth is also possible. This lucky girl.

226
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,740
Ha Eun Ju

227
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:40,930
What is it?

228
00:21:40,930 --> 00:21:42,010
You're not dead.

229
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:43,630
Are you upset that I'm not dead?

230
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:47,750
I'm on a high note right now. Come out.

231
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:53,520
I mean what kind of—

232
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,520
Look at her phone manners.

233
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:58,900
If you tell me to come do you think I'll easily come out?

234
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,670
What do you see me as?

235
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:07,650
Jazz Club
Round About Midnight

236
00:22:09,370 --> 00:22:13,080
It's good manners to listen to what she has to say.

237
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:27,630
Over here, tequila please.

238
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:32,140
It makes me upset. Why do you tell a person to come and go as you please?

239
00:22:36,710 --> 00:22:38,930
What do you have to say?

240
00:22:39,890 --> 00:22:41,990
Are you going to end like this?

241
00:22:41,990 --> 00:22:45,170
- What?
- The Sinyeong Philharmonic.

242
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:50,590
The conductor changed the piece. What am I supposed to do?

243
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:53,170
It means I should shut up and leave.

244
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:59,000
So you're going to leave when you're told to. That's it?

245
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:06,720
- All losers are like this.
- What?

246
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:09,510
You think you're so pitiful.

247
00:23:09,510 --> 00:23:12,730
What are you trying to say?

248
00:23:17,710 --> 00:23:19,370
Here.

249
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:27,860
What is it?

250
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:29,980
A part-time job.

251
00:23:29,980 --> 00:23:32,800
They are looking for someone to play timpani to record a movie soundtrack.

252
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:38,020
I brought it for you. I should pay you back for sleeping with Jae Hyeong.

253
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:40,290
Isn't that right?

254
00:23:40,290 --> 00:23:45,680
Why are you like this all of a sudden? Since when did you care for me?

255
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:49,470
I'm going to start caring now.

256
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:54,340
We used to be friends.  Although you might have forgetten.

257
00:24:05,250 --> 00:24:07,200
Violin?

258
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:13,750
- It's Ha Eun Ju.
- Ha Eun Ju?

259
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:19,640
Ha Eun Ju! Ha Eun Ju! Ha Eun Ju!

260
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:22,550
Ha Eun Ju! Ha Eun Ju! Ha Eun Ju!

261
00:24:22,550 --> 00:24:26,540
Ha Eun Ju! Ha Eun Ju! Ha Eun Ju!

262
00:25:29,620 --> 00:25:31,800
One glass please.

263
00:25:33,910 --> 00:25:35,860
Are you letting your anger out?

264
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:44,360
Stop minding my business.

265
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:52,160
What are you doing?

266
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:56,360
Me? I'm worrying about Hong Yi Yeong.

267
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:59,320
I never asked you to worry.

268
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:01,380
This was mine.

269
00:26:01,380 --> 00:26:05,010
I'll pick up the tab. You're unemployed.

270
00:26:11,050 --> 00:26:13,370
Are you done talking?

271
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:20,360
You're right, I am jobless.

272
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:25,420
As you said, I did get fired from the orchestra after one day. Do you feel satisfied?

273
00:26:25,420 --> 00:26:28,370
I was being patient but you're so rude.

274
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:37,170
Don't follow me. I'm in a bad mood.

275
00:26:37,170 --> 00:26:38,520
Why aren't you answering your evening call?

276
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:40,440
I said don't follow me.

277
00:26:40,440 --> 00:26:42,160
Are you never going to talk to me now?

278
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:45,730
Why do I have to talk to you?

279
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:50,470
Why are you like this to me? Why do you keep bothering me?

280
00:26:50,470 --> 00:26:55,090
Are you stalking me? Or are you seriously interested in me?

281
00:26:55,090 --> 00:26:57,400
I told you I'm very interested in you.

282
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:03,520
We still have a lot to talk about.

283
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:06,310
Please stop following me.

284
00:27:06,310 --> 00:27:09,300
Yesterday at Namsan, you cried and even fainted,

285
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:12,350
and I saw that, so how do expect me to stay still?

286
00:27:13,250 --> 00:27:15,540
I don't know, I don't remember anything.

287
00:27:15,540 --> 00:27:19,410
Stop following me. If you keep following me, I'm going to report you.

288
00:27:26,910 --> 00:27:29,630
What is up with that guy? Why does he keep following me?

289
00:27:29,630 --> 00:27:32,420
What does he have to do with me?

290
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:37,180
How did he know how to find me?

291
00:27:40,510 --> 00:27:43,000
How did he know I was here?

292
00:27:58,240 --> 00:28:01,950
Surely he's not following me...

293
00:28:01,950 --> 00:28:04,220
No, it can't be.

294
00:28:04,220 --> 00:28:07,810
He's not a stalker, why would he?

295
00:28:07,810 --> 00:28:12,160
But why am I running away?

296
00:28:34,490 --> 00:28:39,210
Jang Yun, what kind of person is he?

297
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:45,810
Jang Yun

298
00:28:57,730 --> 00:29:00,190
Pianist Jang Yun

299
00:29:02,020 --> 00:29:05,070
This person is like a ghost.

300
00:29:05,070 --> 00:29:07,860
How can there be no information about him?

301
00:29:12,780 --> 00:29:16,020
He isn't in social media either?

302
00:29:16,020 --> 00:29:19,250
I mean he might not do it.

303
00:29:24,980 --> 00:29:27,270
Seriously this person, really...

304
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:29,770
It's so late.

305
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:48,360
What is this?

306
00:29:50,730 --> 00:29:53,410
No way, is it him?

307
00:29:59,350 --> 00:30:01,290
What is that?

308
00:30:10,230 --> 00:30:13,300
Blood? Blood?

309
00:30:26,300 --> 00:30:27,110
You came.

310
00:30:27,110 --> 00:30:30,130
What do you mean you came? Did you know I was coming?

311
00:30:30,130 --> 00:30:32,370
I played the piano so that you would come.

312
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:37,360
How was it?

313
00:30:38,150 --> 00:30:40,260
- What was?
- Schubert.

314
00:30:40,260 --> 00:30:44,220
I just played this instead of rice cakes as a moving-in offering.

315
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:46,320
He's so shameless.

316
00:30:47,690 --> 00:30:49,570
Do you even know what time it is?

317
00:30:49,570 --> 00:30:54,090
Don't you think it's ignorant to play the piano this late?

318
00:30:54,100 --> 00:30:58,100
I did think of that.  Do you think I don't know at least that much?

319
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:06,920
I was cleaning the bathroom and hurt myself.

320
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:11,320
Not crossing over my veranda? This shameless guy.

321
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:15,180
Look at this.. the size is perfect.

322
00:31:15,180 --> 00:31:17,100
I was listening to those soles.

323
00:31:17,100 --> 00:31:18,210
Do you want to come in?

324
00:31:18,210 --> 00:31:20,470
What did you say? Wait, what did you say?

325
00:31:20,470 --> 00:31:24,320
To my house. I can give you a call personally.

326
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:25,030
Evening call.

327
00:31:25,030 --> 00:31:28,000
I'm not in the mood to joke around.

328
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:32,190
Do you really think I'm a stalker?

329
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:39,700
Who said that...?

330
00:31:40,780 --> 00:31:43,630
The doctor said so.

331
00:31:43,630 --> 00:31:46,870
The man you keep bumping into

332
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:51,470
is a stalker.

333
00:31:59,850 --> 00:32:03,360
Don't worry. I'm not a stalker
